<br>
For example taking into account that these 'no-drop' items we're paying for are readily sold in EC - or that a melee can use a low grade weapon and still hit a mob, whilst a caster using low level spells may not be able to land it on the mob...to simply treat spells as weapons or armour would be facile. <br>
<br>
I can see the raid conversations now...<br>
/gu KEI has dropped - tells if you want to roll, 10rpp<br>
/tell gu I'm not rolling<br>
/gu You need it, the raid wants you to have it, roll on it<br>
/tell gu I can't afford it, sorry - make do with C2<br>
<br>
Who benefits?<br>
<br>
But my personal view is that spells are our tools just as much as weapons are the tools of melees - with arguably one big advantage in our favour - I would rather be a nekkid caster on a CR than a nekkid melee.<br>
<br>
